<div class="hidden"><h1>getCookie()</h1>
		<p>To retrieve data stored in a cookie sent to the client through <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/addcookie/" target="_self">addCookie()</a> (or the class constructor), simply pass the $name of the cookie to <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/getcookie/" target="_self">getCookie()</a>, and the value will be returned if it is available.<br />
<br />
If the C<span class="the_R">R</span>NRSTN Suite :: has been initialized via <a href="../../../classes/crnrstn/initcookieencryption/" target="_self">initCookieEncryption()</a> to apply an encryption layer to the cookie management process, there are special methods for encryption that must be used. See examples and documentation on the following: <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/addencryptedcookie/" target="_self">addEncryptedCookie()</a>, <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/getencryptedcookie/" target="_self">getEncryptedCookie()</a> and <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/deleteencryptedcookie/" target="_self">deleteEncryptedCookie()</a>.</p>
		<p>Version: </p>
		<p>Method Definition: getcookie($name)</p>
		<p>Invoking class: cookie_manager</p><h2>Technical Specifications:<h2><p>Data stored in cookies created by calling <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/addencryptedcookie/" target="_self">addEncryptedCookie()</a> can only be retrieved with <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/getencryptedcookie/" target="_self">getEncryptedCookie()</a>. getCookie() will not return useful cookie data where encryption has been used.</p><p>It is recommended that you upgrade to the latest version of PHP to take advantage of the latests gains in security and processing efficiency.</p><p>Currently tested on an ubuntu 4.2 server running PHP Version 5.2.6 and Apache 2.2.11</p><h2>Parameters:</h2><h3>$name</h3><p>The name of the cookie. <br />
<br />
Please see php.net for additional information.</p><p>Last upated: 2017-04-11 02:27:21</p></div>